#: setup_game:2
msgid "[TITLE]The Manual: Preparing For The Journey[/TITLE]"
msgstr ""

#: setup_game:2
msgid ""
"Now that the world has been generated, it's time to prepare your settlers to travel.  There are three main screens.\n"
"Instructions for which keys to press are displayed at the bottom of each screen."
msgstr ""

#: setup_game:5
msgid ""
"The Site Selection Screen shows you where your fortress is located, and the "
"general characteristics of the surrounding area.  You can place your "
"fortress in any location so long as the selection rectangle isn't entirely "
"in an ocean, lake or mountain biome."
msgstr ""

#: setup_game:7
msgid ""
"The Unit Preparation Screen has a list of the dwarves that are going on the journey and their skills.\n"
"Dwarves learn as they work, so it's not essential to spend a lot of points here, but you might find it convenient to\n"
"let them know what their main roles are at this point by making them novices in a few skills.  For instance, if you make\n"
"one of the dwarves a \"Novice Miner\", then that dwarf will immediately grab a pick and take any mining orders you prepare."
msgstr ""

#: setup_game:12
msgid ""
"You buy skills with points.  Keep in mind that the skill list scrolls.\n"
"The amount of points you have is displayed on the lower right.\n"
"These points are also used to buy equipment on the Equipment Preparation Screen."
msgstr ""

#: setup_game:16
msgid ""
"The Equipment Preparation Screen is the most complicated of the three screens.  The list of objects your dwarves are bringing along appears on the left, and the list of animals going on the journey appears on the right.  If you choose to add a new object, you'll be taken to a screen with a list of all the potential items that you can bring.  Type in a partial name to narrow the list.\n"
"You can leave this screen by selecting an object or by pressing [IKEY:LEAVESCREEN]."
msgstr ""

#: storage:2
msgid "[TITLE]The Manual: Storage[/TITLE]"
msgstr "[TITLE]The Manual: Armazenamento[/TITLE]"

#: storage:2
msgid ""
"If you aren't careful, your fortress can become a cluttered and inefficient mess.\n"
"In fact, you'll find one of your principal roles in managing the fortress is to get food, materials and finished goods to\n"
"move around efficiently."
msgstr ""

#: storage:6
msgid ""
"The main method for moving objects around is the designation of stockpiles.  A stockpile has certain object types associated to it,\n"
"and any object that isn't already stored will be brought to a free space in the pile when a dwarf with the proper hauling profession\n"
"has some free time."
msgstr ""

#: storage:12
msgid ""
"Using the mastery option, you can make piles take objects from other piles to create a flow of goods throughout\n"
"the fortress."
msgstr ""

#: storage:16
msgid "[LINK:data/help/menu_stockpiles]Designating Stockpiles[/LINK]"
msgstr ""

#: storage:19
msgid "[C:7:0:1]Bins[C:7:0:0]"
msgstr ""

#: storage:15
msgid ""
"Stockpiles fill up quickly.  In order to consolidate objects and save space,"
" dwarves use bins."
msgstr ""

#: storage:22
msgid ""
"Once you make a bin, the dwarves will move it to a furniture stockpile.  The"
" next time a bin is needed, a dwarf will place an object in the bin, and "
"then the bin will be moved to the proper stockpile.  All you have to do is "
"provide a consistent supply of bins."
msgstr ""

#: storage:25
msgid "[C:7:0:1]Barrels[C:7:0:0]"
msgstr "[C:7:0:1]Barris[C:7:0:0]"

#: storage:24
msgid ""
"Barrels are exactly like bins, but they are used for food.  Food in barrels "
"is less susceptible to pests, though barrels are not immune to their clever "
"and persistent vermin natures."
msgstr ""

#: storage:29
msgid "[C:7:0:1]Personal Storage[C:7:0:0]"
msgstr "[C:7:0:1]Armazenamento Pessoal[C:7:0:0]"

#: storage:28
msgid ""
"Dwarves will amass personal property over time, especially when the coin "
"economy begins in the middle game.  If a dwarf has a room, you'll soon find "
"that personal possessions cover the floor.  In order to give the dwarf more "
"storage space, consider placing a chest and a cabinet within the room.  "
"Cabinets are used for storing clothes, and chests are used to store "
"everything else.  Certain important dwarves will require weapon and armor "
"racks in their rooms as well."
msgstr ""

